                <note rend="inline" type="source">362.115 St 21/432: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-02T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 2—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>371. [From Hill.] H–152. Department’s H–80<note n="18" xml:id="d114fn18">Not
                        printed.</note> received while in Reparation Commission meeting today.</p>
                <p>Commission decided to attribute tankers to Great Britain and indicated
                    willingness that that Government should arrange with us for delivery. British
                    delegation believes British Board of Trade will act. I will confirm this.
                    Hill.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
